"red, green, blue\n"
": The blur intensity for each of the RGB channels.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: title
#: content/views/darkroom/modules/dithering.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "dithering"
msgstr "bruigo"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/views/darkroom/modules/dithering.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "This module eliminates some of the banding artifacts that can result when Ansel's internal 32-bit floating point data is transferred into discrete 8-bit or 16-bit integer output format for display or export.\n"
msgstr "Ĉi tiu modulo evitas iujn el la bandaj artefaktoj, kiuj povas rezulti kiam la internaj 32-bitaj glitkomaj datumoj de Ansel estas transdonitaj al diskreta 8-bita aŭ 16-bita entjera eliga formato por montriĝo aŭ eksportado.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/views/darkroom/modules/dithering.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Although not an inherent problem in any of Ansel's modules, some operations may provoke banding if they produce a lightness gradient in the image. To mitigate possible artifacts you should consider activating dithering when using the [_vignetting_](./vignetting.md) or [_graduated density_](./graduated-density.md) modules. This is especially relevant for images with extended homogeneous areas such as cloudless sky. Also watch out for banding artifacts when using a gradient [drawn mask](../masking-and-blending/masks/drawn).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/views/darkroom/modules/dithering.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Viewing an image dithered into a very low bit depth from some distance (e.g. “Floyd-Steinberg 1-bit b&w”) will give the impression of a homogeneous grayscale image. Ansel attempts to mimic this impression when rendering zoomed-out images in the center view, the navigation window and thumbnails. This is accomplished by dithering those images into a higher number of grayscale levels. Note that, as a consequence, the [scopes](../../toolboxes/scopes.md) module -- the data for which is derived from the navigation window -- will show this increased number of levels and is therefore not a full match to the output image.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/views/darkroom/modules/dithering.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"method\n"
": Choose the dithering method to use.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/views/darkroom/modules/dithering.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ": _Floyd-Steinberg_: Systematically distribute quantization errors over neighboring pixels. This method can be selected with some typical output bit depths. Alternatively, you can select _Floyd-Steinberg auto_, which automatically adapts to the desired output format.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/views/darkroom/modules/dithering.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ": _random dithering_: This method just adds some level of randomness to break sharp tonal value bands.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/views/darkroom/modules/dithering.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"damping (\"random\" method only)\n"
": Controls the level of added random noise expressed as a damping factor in a 10*log 2 basis. A value of -80 is a good fit for 8-bit output formats; -160 for 16-bit output.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: title
#: content/views/darkroom/modules/raw-chromatic-aberrations.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "raw chromatic aberrations"
msgstr "krudaj kromataj aberacioj"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/views/darkroom/modules/raw-chromatic-aberrations.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Correct chromatic aberrations of raw images.\n"
