#. type: Plain text
#: content/preferences-settings/darkroom.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"show the guides widget in modules UI\n"
": Enable this to show the local [guides & overlays](../views/toolboxes/guides-overlays.md#local-guides) interface directly within the UI of the modules that support it (default on).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/preferences-settings/darkroom.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"show right-side buttons in processing module headers\n"
": Choose whether to show the four buttons (mask indicator, multi-instance menu, reset, presets menu) on the right-hand-side of the module header for processing modules. These buttons will always appear when the mouse is over the module. At other times they will be shown or hidden according to this preference selection:\n"
": - _always_: always show all buttons\n"
": - _active_: only show the buttons when the mouse is over the module\n"
": - _dim_: buttons are dimmed when mouse is not over the module\n"
": - _auto_: hide the buttons when the panel is narrow\n"
": - _fade_: fade out all buttons when the panel narrows\n"
": - _fit_: hide all the buttons if the module name doesn't fit\n"
": - _smooth_: fade out all buttons in one header simultaneously\n"
": - _glide_: gradually hide individual buttons as needed\n"
": (default _always_)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/preferences-settings/darkroom.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"prompt for name on addition of new instance\n"
": If enabled, when creating a new instance of a processing module, a prompt will be immediately displayed allowing you to set a name for the new instance (default on).\n"
msgstr ""

