#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/printing-labeled-images.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "- `ipairs` is a standard lua function that will iterate through all numeric indices of a table. We use it here because Ansel's database has non-numeric indices which are functions to manipulate the database itself (adding or deleting images, for example).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/printing-labeled-images.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "- Iterating through a table will return both the key and the value used. It is conventional in lua to use a variable named “`_`” to store values that we don't care about.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/printing-labeled-images.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "- Note that we use the standard lua function `tostring` here and not the Ansel-specific `Ansel.debug.dump`. The standard function will return a name for the object whereas the debug function will print the content. The debug function would be too verbose here. Once again, it is a great debug tool but it should not be used for anything else.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: title
#: content/lua/sharing-scripts.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "sharing scripts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/sharing-scripts.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "So far, all of our lua code has been in _luarc_. That's a good way to develop your script but not very practical for distribution. We need to make this into a proper lua module. To do that, we save the code in a separate file (`scp-storage.lua` in this case):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: content/lua/sharing-scripts.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"--[[\n"
"SCP STORAGE\n"
"a simple storage to export images via scp\n"
"\n"
"AUTHOR\n"
"Jérémy Rosen (jeremy.rosen@enst-bretagne.fr)\n"
"\n"
"INSTALLATION\n"
"* copy this file in $CONFIGDIR/lua/ where CONFIGDIR\n"
"is your Ansel configuration directory\n"
"* add the following line in the file $CONFIGDIR/luarc\n"
"  require \"scp-storage\"\n"
"\n"
"USAGE\n"
"* select \"Export via SCP\" in the storage selection menu\n"
"* set the target directory\n"
"* export your images\n"
"\n"
"LICENSE\n"
"GPLv2\n"
"\n"
"]]\n"
"Ansel = require \"Ansel\"\n"
"Ansel.configuration.check_version(...,{2,0,0})\n"
"\n"
"local scp_path = Ansel.new_widget(\"entry\"){\n"
"  tooltip =\"Complete path to copy to. Can include user and hostname\",\n"
"  text = \"\",\n"
"  reset_callback = function(self) self.text = \"\" end\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"Ansel.register_storage(\"scp_export\",\"Export via scp\",\n"
"  function( storage, image, format, filename,\n"
"     number, total, high_quality, extra_data)\n"
"    if coroutine.yield(\"RUN_COMMAND\",\"scp \"..filename..\" \"..\n"
"      scp_path.text\n"
"    ) then\n"
"      Ansel.print_error(\"scp failed for \"..tostring(image))\n"
"    end\n"
"    end,\n"
"    nil, --finalize\n"
"    nil, --supported\n"
"    nil, --initialize\n"
"    Ansel.new_widget(\"box\") {\n"
"    orientation =\"horizontal\",\n"
"    Ansel.new_widget(\"label\"){label = \"target SCP PATH \"},\n"
"    scp_path,\n"
"})\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/sharing-scripts.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Ansel will look for scripts (following the normal lua rules) in the standard directories plus `$CONFIGDIR/lua/*.lua`. So our script can be called by simply adding `require \"scp-storage\"` in the _luarc_ file. A couple of extra notes...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/sharing-scripts.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "- The function `Ansel.configuration.check_version` will check compatibility for you. The \"`...`\" will turn into your script's name and `{2,0,0}` is the API version you have tested your script with. You can add multiple API versions if you update your script for multiple versions of Ansel.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/sharing-scripts.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "- Make sure to declare all your functions as `local` so as not to pollute the general namespace.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/sharing-scripts.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "- Make sure you do not leave debug prints in your code -- `Ansel.print_error` in particular allows you to leave debug prints in your final code without disturbing the console.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/sharing-scripts.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "- You are free to choose any license for your script but scripts that are uploaded on Ansel's website need to be GPLv2.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/sharing-scripts.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once you have filled all the fields, checked your code, you can upload it to our script page [here](https://github.com/darktable-org/lua-scripts).\n"
msgstr ""

